I think the ExtractorJS code is assuming that a &#39;via&#39; URI will be
available to serve as the implied base HREF. This is usually
the case for Javascript content, but should not be assumed.

I don&#39;t think any recent (just before 1.6) changes would have made
this error more common; is there any chance you&#39;ve recently started
using a larger seed list or manually feeding more URIs into a running
crawl (such that URIs returning Javascript would lack &#39;via&#39; URIs)?

In any case, it&#39;s a bug -- if no &#39;via&#39; is available the URI from
which the Javascript itself was returned is probably the next
best &#39;base&#39; to use for derelativizing relative URIs.

- Gordon @ IA

